This paper is about deep clustering, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper focuses on two methods, IMSAT and IIC, which are used for clustering images and jointly learning feature representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses transformations and losses, which are important topics in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), so cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses adversarial examples, which are commonly used in neural networks, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
